In the annexed drawings, like reference characters indicate like elements throughout.


FIG. 1 is a diagrammatic view of a rack warehouse in which an embodiment of the transfer device of the invention finds application, the load being centered with respect to the forklift carrying the same;


FIGS. 2 and 3 are views similar to that of FIG. 1 showing sequential steps for the load transfer from the forklift to the rack cell;


FIG. 4 is a top plan view of the transfer device of the invention with some parts broken to show under lying elements;


FIG. 5 is a partially broken side elevation of the transfer device;


FIG. 6 is a longitudinal section taken a long line 6--6 of FIG. 4


FIGS. 7 and 8 are cross-sections taken along line 7--7 and 8--8 of FIG. 4 respectively;


FIGS. 9, 10 and 11 are partial elevations of the end of the mainframe showing the sequential steps for hooking the mainframe to the anchor bar of the rack; and


FIG. 12 is an enlarged top plan view of the underframe of FIG. 4.
